<article class="comment" id="comment5747995" data-author="users/55531" data-subject="comments/5747995" data-dislikes="2" data-id="5747995">
<p class="avatar"><a rel="nofollow" title="Royalblues" href="/users/Royalblues"><img class="framed lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MCA4MCI+PC9zdmc+" width="80" height="80" data-original="https://images.pushsquare.com/users/55531/avatar.jpg?v=1369767867" alt="Royalblues" /></a></p>
<div class="detail"><ul class="info"><li class=" first"><a class="num" rel="nofollow" href="news/2020/08/reaction_sony_wants_ps5_to_be_the_best_place_to_play_and_itll_open_its_wallet_to_achieve_it#comment5747995">17</a></li><li><a rel="nofollow" class="username accent" title="Royalblues" href="/users/Royalblues">Royalblues</a></li><li class=" last"><time class="date age " datetime="2020-08-04T14:18:35+00:00"><span>Tue 4th Aug 2020</span></time></li></ul>
<section class="text">
<p>Microsoft knows they will lose this generation, so they will make the money back through their services, as opposed to their hardware alone. It is still a good business model, because no matter how badlt they screwed up, in a few years time, people will see the console for the beast it is and start to buy it more.</p><p>And regardless of the initial reaction to the presentation, millions of people will still buy it.</p><p>These guys are playing the long game, making sure they are firmly entrenched in game streaming technology for whenever the industry is ready to catch up. They are really they only ones with that capability right now. This is basically their plan right now.</p></section>
